	<body>
		<div class="mcontent">
			<h1>League Information</h1>
			<div class="break"></div>
			<h2>1v1 League Format</h2>
			<div class="break"></div>
			<p>Layout</p>
			<br/>
			<ul class="normal">
				<li>The league separates players by Code and Division.</li>
				<li>Each Division consists of Groups, and Groups consist of 10-13 players each</li>
				<li>Within a group, players will play a single round robin schedule.</li>
				<li>A match will consist of a best of 3 games format.</li>
				<li>Games that result in draws must be played again.</li>
				<li>Maps for each match will be given ahead of time.</li>
				<li>At the end of a season, the top 3 players in each group are promoted to a higher code or division, and the 
					bottom 3 players in each group are relegated to a lower code or division based on final standings.</li>
				<li>The bottom 6 players of Code SP are relegated after each season.</li>
				<li>The bottom 4 players of each group in Code S are relegated after each season.</li>
			</ul>
			<br/>
			<p>Match Schedule</p>
			<br/>
			<ul class="normal">
				<li>A personal schedule of matches will be available to each player once registration is closed.</li>
				<li>Each player will play 2 matches per week.</li>
				<li>Players will contact opponents to schedule a match time. Beware of time zone differences!</li>
			</ul>
			<br/>
			<p>Map Pool</p>
			<br/>
			<ul class="normal">
        		<li>A "Map Pack" is a selection of 3 maps for a BO3 match where the maps will be taken from the map pool.</li>
        		<li>Search for the maps on Battle.net using the Listed Name and Author. Do not use maps from different authors!</li>
        	</ul>
        	<br/>
			<p>Match Results</p>
			<br/>
			<ul class="normal">
				<li>Players will report match results.</li>
				<li>Standings are determined by number of match wins.</li>
				<li>If players are tied on number of match wins, the tiebreaker is game differential.</li>
				<li>If a player does not show up for a match, the player must forfeit with a 2-0 game result.</li>
				<li>Players must report scores for BOTH matches for the week by Sunday at 11:59pm EDT.</li>
				<li>If a player messages an opponent and he does not respond by the due date,  your opponent automatically forfeits and you may report a 2-0 win.</li>
				<li>If your opponent responds to your message without enough time to schedule a game before the due date, you may schedule a makeup and report the score before the next week's due date.</li>
				<li>Disconnects are automatic losses unless both players agree to rematch or if both players can agree on a clear winner before the disconnect occurred.</li>
			</ul>
			<br/>
			<p>Player Conduct</p>
			<br/>
			<ul class="normal">
				<li>This is a friendly league and a community. There is no need to cheat or be dishonest.</li>
				<li>Be respectful and GL HF!</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
